sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_sections
FROM sections
ORDER BY created_at;

external_knowledge:
- "Blossoms" refer to students in the educational context;
- "Nurtured by their mentors" refers to the number of comments made by instructors;
- "Actively engaged in various groups" refers to the number of teams the students have joined;
- "Most recent grade" refers to the latest grade recorded for each student in the specified section.

- "sections" represent different classes or courses within an educational institution;
- "student_teams" represent the teams of students enrolled in these sections;
- "section_instructors" and "instructors" tables provide information about the instructors assigned to each section.

- 'Top 5' refers to the highest-ranked students within each section;
- 'Average exam grades' are calculated for each student in each section;
- 'Section' refers to a specific class or course.

- 'Spring 2023' is a specific academic term;
- 'blossoms' metaphorically refers to students who performed well;
- 'shone the brightest' implies having the highest average grades;
- 'petals' metaphorically represents the number of grades received.

- "section_name" refers to the name of the section, akin to the name of a room in a library;
- "section_type" refers to the type of the section, such as lecture, discussion, or lab;
- "average grade" is calculated by averaging the grades of all students in a section;
- "number of students" is the count of distinct students in each section;
- "last updated" refers to the most recent timestamp when the section information was modified.

- Students who have joined teams are those with a status of 'joined' in the `student_teams` table;
- The average grade is calculated across all sections a student is part of;
- The results are ordered by student ID and the order of sections they are part of.

- "section_type" can include types such as lecture, discussion, and lab;
- "academic_term" refers to specific periods such as semesters or quarters;
- The average grade is rounded to two decimal places.

- 'garden of Advanced Database Systems' refers to the section named 'Advanced Database Systems';
- 'young saplings' are the students in the teams;
- 'average height' refers to the average grade of the students.

- 'Stars of Section A' refers to students in Section A;
- 'Shining grades' refers to the grades of the students;
- 'From the brightest to the least luminous' means the grades are ordered in descending order.
